An Amazon Web Services Application Load Balancer (ALB) in front of the web tier.
EC2 Auto Scaling Groups for the web and application tiers.
Multi-AZ subnets and RDS Multi-AZ for high availability.
IAM roles instead of long-lived AWS access keys.
AWS Systems Manager Session Manager instead of SSH access.
Separate route tables for public and private subnets with a NAT Gateway for outbound internet access from private instances.
AWS Secrets Manager or AWS Systems Manager Parameter Store for database credentials.
CloudWatch logs, alarms, and monitoring.
S3 for static assets and backups.
HTTPS using AWS Certificate Manager with the ALB.
Infrastructure as Code using CloudFormation or Terraform for easier maintenance and repeatable deployments.


