# Complete Linux Administration Workflow

```text
Linux Server
      │
      ▼
Python Script Starts
      │
      ├── Create Users
      ├── Set File Permissions
      ├── Install Packages
      ├── Start Services
      ├── Monitor CPU
      ├── Monitor RAM
      ├── Monitor Disk
      ├── Analyze Logs
      ├── Generate Reports
      ├── Create Backup
      └── Schedule Cron Jobs
```

## Daily Python Projects Used by Linux Administrators

| Project                 | Python Modules       | Real-Life Use                         |
| ----------------------- | -------------------- | ------------------------------------- |
| Server Health Dashboard | `psutil`, `pandas`   | Monitor CPU, RAM, Disk                |
| User Creation Tool      | `subprocess`         | Onboard employees                     |
| File Backup Utility     | `shutil`, `datetime` | Scheduled backups                     |
| Log Analyzer            | File I/O             | Troubleshoot application errors       |
| Package Installer       | `subprocess`         | Provision new servers                 |
| Service Manager         | `subprocess`         | Start, stop, restart services         |
| Network Monitor         | `psutil`             | Monitor bandwidth and connections     |
| Performance Reporter    | `pandas`, `csv`      | Generate daily infrastructure reports |
| Cleanup Script          | `os`, `shutil`       | Delete temporary and old log files    |
| Deployment Automation   | `subprocess`, `os`   | Deploy applications to Linux servers  |

These examples represent the kinds of Python automation scripts commonly written by Linux system administrators, DevOps engineers, Site Reliability Engineers (SREs), and Cloud Engineers to manage production Linux servers.

